What is the projected market size & growth rate of the Diagnostics Telematics Market?

Market Analysis and Insights:

Global Diagnostics Telematics Market

The diagnostics telematics market is expected to witness market growth at a rate of 27.10% in the forecast period of 2021 to 2028 and is expected to reach USD 28,345.20 billion by 2028. Data Bridge Market Research report on diagnostics telematics market provides analysis and insights regarding the various factors expected to be prevalent throughout the forecast period while providing their impacts on the marketâ€™s growth. The rise in the development of smart transportation system is escalating the growth of diagnostics telematics market.

Telematics is the technological solution utilized for long-distance transmission of information in commercial automobiles. The solution is utilized for monitoring the location and movement of vehicles through global positioning systems (GPS) and on-board diagnostic systems in order to track vehicle diagnostics. They also monitor trailers and non-motorized assets and alerting the fleet manager in case of any unauthorized movement. They are known to provide maintenance insights and safety tracking and insurance risk assessment. Insurance providers make the use of this technology to monitor driver behavior for the determination of insurance policies accordingly.

The increasing initiatives by the government for the development of intelligent transportation system rise in the demand for smartphone features in the car and automated driving technologies and increasing need for passenger safety features are the major factors driving the growth of diagnostics telematics market. The availability of mobility integrators because of the integrated transportation network of shared and private cars as well as other modes of transportation, use of these automotive systems to tackle system failures in case of communication breakdown and high acceptance of telematics among consumers and the emergence of regulatory initiatives taken by the government for security and safety accelerate the diagnostics telematics market growth. The development of systems including vehicular emergency warning systems, driving assistance systems, automatic driving systems, global positioning system (GPS) navigation and wireless safety communications and the demand for into intelligent transportation systems (ITS) and wireless access for vehicular environment (WAVE) and the use of systems for trailer tracking and automobile insurance further influence the diagnostics telematics market. Additionally, the use of systems for trailer tracking and automobile insurance, rising occurrences of road accidents and developments in 5G connectivity positively affect the diagnostics telematics market. Furthermore, development of diverse and variant telematics systems will create profitable opportunities to the diagnostics telematics market players in the forecast period of 2021 to 2028.

On the other hand, complexities owing to communication breakdowns and error rates and high cost associated with the systems are factors expected to obstruct the diagnostics telematics market growth. The rise in concerns regarding the sensitivity of a single error causing heavy and serious breakdowns is projected to challenge the diagnostics telematics market in the forecast period of 2021 to 2028.

